<h1>Teddy Bear Museum (free)</h1>
<p>This area of the island has a lot of resorts and attractions for families and is very touristy/western. We passed on 'Play-Kpop-Jeju", an attraction with holographic music shows, history exhibits & a be-the-star experience. Maybe I will prepare next year by listening to a lot of K-pop over the next 4-6 monyths. museum attraction (thank God) and took the kids to the Teddy Bear Musuem. They were celebrating its 20th anniversary, so admission was free for adults and children. And it was pouring rain, so perfect time for an indoor activity. Everything and every famous person you can imagine, from Disney World, to Michael Jordan, Tiger Woods, Steve Jobs, Muhammed Ali, The Beatles, and Neil Armstrong, this museum puts a cute teddy bear face on every big name in human history. (Such a Korean thing to do). There's even a live music show, with a teddy-version Elvis performing some of his greatest hits. I guess Teddy bears are so popular in Korea that there are multiple locations. See <a href='http://www.teddybearmuseum.com/site/' target="_blank">website for more info</a>.)</p>


